The salad is chopped lettuce, regular red peppers, roasted red peppers, cucumbers, sweetcorn and black beans all tossed together.
I made a dressing using fresh lime juice, honey, cumin, chopped garlic, salt and pepper.
The tortilla strips (totopos?) You just cut up regular tortillas, coat with a bit of salt and oil and toss them in a high heat oven until they're crispy.
